type.description: Determines whether a single or multiple items can be pressed at a time.

modelValue.description: The controlled value of the pressed items. Can be binded with v-model.

defaultValue.description: The value of the item to show as pressed when initially rendered and type is "single". Use when you do not need to control the state of the items.

disabled.description: When true, prevents the user from interacting with the toggle group and all its items.

as.description: The element or component this component should render as. Can be overwrite by asChild

asChild.description: Change the default rendered element for the one passed as a child, merging their props and behavior.
